The paper deals with the representation of combinatorial objects, specifically interval graphs, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of geometry in the representation suggests that it could also fall under computational geometry (cs.CG). The algorithmic aspect of the paper, specifically the recognition problem, suggests that it could also belong to data structures (cs.DS) and complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of the sunflower case, which is a concept in graph theory, suggests that it could also belong to graph theory (cs.GT).
